. Hi guys,

There has been a bit confusion on how required is being used and it will be cleaned up after next release of Formsy.

The prop `validations` uses validation rules to set errors. The prop `required` can also use validation rules to indicate when an input should be required.

So:

``` js
// When the value of the input is `false`, showRequired() will give true
<MyInput name="some_field" type="text" required="isFalse">

// When the value of the input is falsy (empty string etc), showRequired() will give true
<MyInput name="some_field" type="text" required>

// showRequired() will always be false 
<MyInput name="some_field" type="text">
```

So what we need to clean up here is maybe use a new property. Just throwing it out there:

``` js
<MyInput name="some_field" type="text" required={true/false} requiredRule="isFalse">
```

But yeah, I hope this explained how it works now.
