. Hi @burtyish,

Actually, the input itself does not need a name attribute. Create your own credit card info formsy element, something like:

``` javascript
var CreditCardInfoInput = React.createClass({
  mixins: [Formsy.Mixin],
  updateValue: function (event) {
    this.setValue(event.target.value);
  },
  render: function () {
    return <input value={this.getValue()} onChange={this.updateValue}/>
  }
});
```

This wraps your plain input, without a name attribute, into a formsy element. You can now use it like this:

``` javascript
<Formsy.Form>
  <CreditCardInfoInput name="creditcardinfo"/>
</Formsy.Form>
```

The name attribute used here has nothing to do with the input inside. It is just a property on the **CreditCardInfoInput** component that Formsy will use to identify the property name for the value. So you are following the guidelines with this solution.

