It might seem a bit aggressive to do the validation on each key press, though as I understand it you mean that from a user experience perspective, not a technical perspective?

I would suggest that you add your own state to your form element. Something like, `showValidation`. That way you can choose with onBlur or Enter to set that state to true and combine it with the internal methods of Formsy. Like:

``` js
var MyInput = React.createClass({
  mixins: [Formsy.Mixin],
  getInitialState: function () {
    return {
      showValidation: false
    },
    onInputChange: function (event) {
      this.setValue(event.target.value);
    },
    onInputBlur: function () {
      this.setState({
        showValidation: true
      });
    },
    onInputFocus: function () {
      this.setState({
        showValidation: false
      });
    },
    render: function () {
      return (
        <div>
          <input onChange={this.onInputChange} value={this.getValue()}/>
          <div>{this.showError() && this.state.showValidation ? this.getErrorMessage() : null}</div>
        </div>
      );
    }
  }
});
```

Would that make sense?

I do not think it is a good idea to grab value from DOM node as it breaks with the principles of React. The state of the component defines what is in the UI, not the other way around. I am sure we can find a solution for this :-)

Let me know if I misunderstood any needs and we can keep working towards a solution!
