I'm also in need of this. If you try to force re-validation in `componentWillReceiveProps()` with `this.props._validate(this);` it causes an infinite loop because the validate function causes a re-render of the component, which calls `componentWillReceiveProps()` again, and so on.

The way to do this that won't result in an infinite loop is to only re-validate on a condition that will be true on the first render, but not on subsequent renders. In my case I am altering the `required` prop so in `componentWillReceiveProps()`:

``` javascript
componentWillReceiveProps: function (newProps) {
    if (newProps.required != this.props.required) {
        // force re-validation because the validation requirements have changed
        this.props._validate(this); 
    }
}
```

You could do the same thing with `newProps.validations != this.props.validations`. 
